Project Structure
HTML - Basic structure of the quiz application.
CSS - Styles for a clean and responsive interface.
JavaScript - Quiz logic to display questions, check answers and calculate scores.

Code Description
HTML: Defines the basic structure of the quiz interface, including a container for questions and options, as well as buttons to advance or restart the quiz.

CSS: Applies styles to make the interface visually appealing and responsive, with buttons for correct and incorrect answers highlighted.

JavaScript:

Defines an array of questions, options, and correct answers.

Manages the state of the quiz, including displaying questions, checking answers, updating scores, and transitioning to the next question.

Handles quiz completion, showing the final result and offering the option to restart the quiz.